my to support their work. (…) At length, after a terrible struggle, the Troops prevailed over the Citizens. (…) This power is to last as long as the Parisians think proper. (…) [315] To secure them further, they have a strong corps of <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Irregular_military" title="Irregular military" id="mwA9E">irregulars</a>, ready armed. Thousands of those Hell-hounds called Terrorists, whom they had shut up in Prison on their last Revolution, as the Satellites of Tyranny, are let loose on the people. (…)"</span></li><li about="#cite_note-23" id="cite_note-23"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-23" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-23" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt78" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Peleg"},"first1":{"wt":"Ilan"},"editor1-last":{"wt":"Stohl"},"editor1-first":{"wt":"Michael"},"editor1-link":{"wt":"Michael Stohl"},"title":{"wt":"The Politics of Terrorism"},"date":{"wt":"1988"},"publisher":{"wt":"CRC Press"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-8247-7814-9"},"page":{"wt":"531"},"edition":{"wt":"Third"},"chapter-url":{"wt":"https://books.google.com/books?id=R60c_2nCcnYC&amp;pg=PA531"},"accessdate":{"wt":"14 February 2019"},"chapter":{"wt":"Terrorism in the Middle East: The Case of the Arab-Israeli Conflict"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwA9I">Peleg, Ilan (1988). <a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://books.google.com/books?id=R60c_2nCcnYC&amp;pg=PA531" id="mwA9M">"Terrorism in the Middle East: The Case of the Arab-Israeli Conflict"</a>.  In <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Michael_Stohl" title="Michael Stohl" id="mwA9Q">Stohl, Michael</a>. <i id="mwA9U">The Politics of Terrorism</i> (Third ed.). CRC Press. p.<span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwA9Y"> </span>531. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard B