"mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt1304" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwBQ4"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-68" id="cite_note-68"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-68" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-68" class="mw-reference-text">Theodore P. Seto <i id="mwBQ8"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://llr.lls.edu/volumes/v35-issue4/seto.pdf" id="mwBRA">The Morality of Terrorism</a></i> Includes a list in <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./The_Times" title="The Times" id="mwBRE">The Times</a> published on 23 July 1946, which were described as Jewish terrorist actions, including those launched by Irgun, of which Begin was a leading member.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-69" id="cite_note-69"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-69" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-69" class="mw-reference-text"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/events/israel_at_50/profiles/81305.stm" id="mwBRI">BBC News: Profiles: Menachem Begin</a> BBC website "Under Begin's command, the underground terrorist group Irgun carried out numerous acts of violence."</span></li><li about="#cite_note-70" id="cite_note-70"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-70" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-70" class="mw-reference-text">Eqbal Ahmad <i id="mwBRM">"<a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-1328039/Straight-talk-on-terrorism.html" id="mwBRQ">Straight talk on terrorism</a>"</i> <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Monthly_Review" title="Monthly Review" id="mwBRU">Monthly Review</a>, January 2002. "including Menachem Begin, appearing in "Wanted" posters saying, "Terrorists, reward this much." The highest reward I have seen offered was 100,000 British pounds for the head of Menachem Begin". <cite class="citation web" about="#mwt224" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"url":{"wt":"http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-1328039/Straight-talk-on-terrorism.html"},"title":{"wt":"Archived copy"},"access-date":{"wt":"2006-09-10"},"deadurl":{"wt":"bot: unknown"},"archiveurl":{"wt":"https://web.archive.org/web/20120205065130/http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-1328039/Straight-talk-on-terrorism.html"},"archivedate":{"wt":"5 February 2012"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwBRY"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20120205065130/http://goliath.ecnext.com/coms2/gi_0199-1328039/Straight-talk-on-terrorism.html" id="mwBRc">"Archived copy"</a>. Archived from the original on 5 February 2012<span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwBRg">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwBRk">2006-09-10</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.btitle=Archived+copy&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fgoliath.ecnext.com%2Fcoms2%2Fgi_0199-1328039%2FStraight-talk-on-terrorism.html&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATerrorism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt224" id="mwBRo"></span><span class="cs1-maint citation-comment" about="#mwt224" id="mwBRs">CS1 maint: Archived copy as title (<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Category:CS1_maint:_Archived_copy_as_title" title="Category:CS1 maint: Archived copy as title" id="mwBRw">link</a>) CS1 maint: BOT: original-url status unknown (<a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Category:CS1_maint:_BOT:_original-url_status_unknown" title="Category:CS1 maint: BOT: original-url status unknown" id="mwBR0">link</a>)</span><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category:CS1_maint:_Archived_copy_as_title" about="#mwt224" id="mwBR4"/><link rel="mw:PageProp/Category" href="./Category: