er 31, 2004. Retrieved April 26, 2007.</span></li><li about="#cite_note-186" id="cite_note-186"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-186" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-186" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation web" about="#mwt962" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite web ","href":"./Template:Cite_web"},"params":{"title":{"wt":"Speech to American Bar Association {{!}} Margaret Thatcher Foundation"},"url":{"wt":"http://www.margaretthatcher.org/document/106096"},"website":{"wt":"www.margaretthatcher.org"},"accessdate":{"wt":"2015-10-05"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB-I"><a rel="mw:ExtLink" class="external text" href="http://www.margaretthatcher.org/document/106096" id="mwB-M">"Speech to American Bar Association | Margaret Thatcher Foundation"</a>. <i id="mwB-Q">www.margaretthatcher.org</i><span class="reference-accessdate" id="mwB-U">. Retrieved <span class="nowrap" id="mwB-Y">2015-10-05</span></span>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Ajournal&amp;rft.genre=unknown&amp;rft.jtitle=www.margaretthatcher.org&amp;rft.atitle=Speech+to+American+Bar+Association+%7C+Margaret+Thatcher+Foundation&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.margaretthatcher.org%2Fdocument%2F106096&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATerrorism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt962" id="mwB-c"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt962" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB-g"/></span></li><li about="#cite_note-187" id="cite_note-187"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-187" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-187" class="mw-reference-text">The researchers found 648 terrorist groups active between 1968 and 2006.  Of those, 136 splintered and 244 were still active in 2006 (Jones and Libicki, 2008, p. 19)</span></li><li about="#cite_note-188" id="cite_note-188"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-188" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-188" class="mw-reference-text">Jones and Libicki (2008, p. 19)</span></li><li about="#cite_note-189" id="cite_note-189"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-189" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-189" class="mw-reference-text">Jones and Libicki (2008, p. 101, Table 5.4)</span></li><li about="#cite_note-190" id="cite_note-190"><a href="./Terrorism#cite_ref-190" rel="mw:referencedBy"><span class="mw-linkback-text">↑ </span></a> <span id="mw-reference-text-cite_note-190" class="mw-reference-text"><cite class="citation book" about="#mwt971" typeof="mw:Transclusion" data-mw='{"parts":[{"template":{"target":{"wt":"cite book ","href":"./Template:Cite_book"},"params":{"last1":{"wt":"Cronin"},"first1":{"wt":"Audrey Kurth"},"title":{"wt":"How Terrorism Ends: Understanding the Decline and Demise of Terrorist Campaigns"},"date":{"wt":"2009"},"publisher":{"wt":"Princeton U. Press"},"isbn":{"wt":"978-0-691-13948-7"}},"i":0}}]}' id="mwB-k">Cronin, Audrey Kurth (2009). <i id="mwB-o">How Terrorism Ends: Understanding the Decline and Demise of Terrorist Campaigns</i>. Princeton U. Press. <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./International_Standard_Book_Number" title="International Standard Book Number" id="mwB-s">ISBN</a><span typeof="mw:Entity" id="mwB-w"> </span><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Special:BookSources/978-0-691-13948-7" title="Special:BookSources/978-0-691-13948-7" id="mwB-0">978-0-691-13948-7</a>.</cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=How+Terrorism+Ends%3A+Understanding+the+Decline+and+Demise+of+Terrorist+Campaigns&amp;rft.pub=Princeton+U.+Press&amp;rft.date=2009&amp;rft.isbn=978-0-691-13948-7&amp;rft.aulast=Cronin&amp;rft.aufirst=Audrey+Kurth&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3ATerrorism" class="Z3988" about="#mwt971" id="mwB-4"></span><link rel="mw-deduplicated-inline-style" href="mw-data:TemplateStyles:r879151008" about="#mwt971" typeof="mw:Extension/templatestyles" data-mw='{"name":"templatestyles","attrs":{"src":"Module:Citation/CS1/styles.css"},"body":{"extsrc":""}}' id="mwB-8"/></span></li></ol></div>

